The energy and enthusiasm at The Pines on the evening of May 11th was absolutely infectious.  Design teams from @conestogacollege presented their vision for a public gathering space at Catalyst137, the subject building of the 2017 CSC Student Design Competition to an audience of AEC professionals at Connections Cafe, an annual networking event sponsored by the Grand Valley Chapter of Construction Specifications Canada.

The 475,000 sq ft building located at 137 Glasgow Street in Kitchener, historically used for warehousing tires and footwear will soon house the world’s largest maker space campus, a hub for the talent, hardware, engineering services and venture capital support needed to build the next generation of IoT companies. .
.
Congratulations to our 3rd year students! Winning the top 4 awards and People's Choice!  Totalling $3,500 in cash awards. .
.
See full article here: https://ssstudio.ca/2017/05/16/catalyst-conestoga-co-op/ .
